org.fest.swing.fixture
Class ContainerFixture<T extends Container>

java.lang.Object
  org.fest.swing.fixture.ComponentFixture<T>
      org.fest.swing.fixture.ContainerFixture<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the type of container handled by this fixture.
Direct Known Subclasses:
JToolBarFixture, WindowFixture
public abstract class ContainerFixture<T extends Container>
extends ComponentFixture<T>

Understands lookup of Components contained in a Container.

Author:
Alex Ruiz

menuItem

public final JMenuItemFixture menuItem(String... path)
Finds a JMenuItem, contained in the Container managed by this fixture, which path matches the given one.

For example, if we are looking for the menu with text "New" contained under the menu with text "File", we can simply call 

 JMenuItemFixture menuItem = container.findMenuItem("File", "Menu");

Parameters:
path - the path of the menu to find.
Returns:
a fixture that manages the JMenuItem found.
Throws:
ComponentLookupException - if a JMenuItem under the given path could not be found.
AssertionError - if the Component found under the given path is not a JMenuItem.
